ajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/2754x1549+0+143/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4e%2F71%2Fe822efa84517b93704cbbe2d2809%2Flajohnson-mckensie-06-toned.jpg" class="img" alt="Garland Jones, recreational therapist and senior program director of the YMCA of South Florida’s special needs program, teaches Mackenzie Wesley, 5, to breathe safely in water by using a ping pong ball as a visual aid." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Garland Jones, recreational therapist and senior program director of the YMCA of South Florida's special needs program, teaches Mackenzie Wesley, 5, to breathe safely in water by using a ping pong ball as a visual aid.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          LA Johnson/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Children with autism are 160 times more likely to die from drowning compared to their peers, according to a 2017 study from Columbia University. This is largely because about half of autistic children have a tendency to wander away from safe environments. That fact, combined with an attraction to water, can be very dangerous. High-quality swim lessons can be a vital preventative measure to combat this issue. Florida, which has one of the highest childhood drowning rates in the nation, expanded a voucher program this month that puts children ages 1-7 who have autism at the front of the line for subsidized swim lessons. The YMCA of South Florida's low-cost Swim Buddies program is one of the largest programs specifically designed for children with disabilities in the area. One of its key features is its focus on individualization and one-on-one instruction, rather than traditional group lessons. Staff members assess each child's needs and tailor the lessons accordingly. Take a look at how this &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2026/07/01/nx-s1-5812852/autism-drowning-florida-swim-lessons-voucher" target="_blank"&gt;program is helping children with autism&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-120361" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 1024;         --source-height: 576;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1024x576+0+107/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fee%2F8f%2F521a6f824e9f9b68c0f4261ba8a9%2Fgettyimages-2260914888.jpg" class="img" alt="Photo Illustration of the new Wegovy 1.5 mg and 4 mg semaglutide tablets with injectable prescription weight loss pens on a white background. Its a prescription medicine used with a reduced calorie diet and physical activity. (Photo by: Michael Siluk/UCG/Universal Images Group via Getty Images)" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Photo Illustration of the new Wegovy 1.5 mg and 4 mg semaglutide tablets with injectable prescription weight loss pens on a white background. Its a prescription medicine used with a reduced calorie diet and physical activity. (Photo by: Michael Siluk/UCG/Universal Images Group via Getty Images)                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Universal Images Group/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;A Medicare pilot program for GLP-1 drugs launched yesterday, allowing beneficiaries to get a &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2026/05/06/nx-s1-5812662/medicare-bridge-glp1-drugs-copay" target="_blank"&gt;weight loss prescription for $50 a month&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Kroger is set to &lt;a href="https://www.wesanews.org/economy-business/2026-07-01/kroger-giant-eagle-grocery" target="_blank"&gt;acquire the Pittsburgh-based Giant Eagle&lt;/a&gt; grocery store chain for $1.65 billion. (via &lt;a href="https://www.wesanews.org/" target="_blank"&gt;WESA&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Dozens of states might be &lt;a href="https://www.kcur.org/environment-agriculture/2026-07-01/snap-error-rates-food-security" target="_blank"&gt;responsible for millions of dollars&lt;/a&gt; next year to help feed low-income families through the federal Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program (SNAP). Under the One Big Beautiful Bill Act, states with error rates of 6% or higher will be required to cover 5%, 10% or 15% of SNAP benefits in the coming years. (via &lt;a href="https://www.kcur.org/" target="_blank"&gt;KCUR&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
