image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1620x911+0+120/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fea%2Ff7%2F3a13ed414fffa6bd68de7ae7a5de%2Fkmills-img-4789.JPG" class="img" alt="Horse mounted riders circle atop a hill at the Battle of Little Bighorn National Monument, near Last Stand Hill, on June 25." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Horse mounted riders circle atop a hill at the Battle of Little Bighorn National Monument, near Last Stand Hill, on June 25.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Kadin Mills/NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On the 150th anniversary of the Battle of Little Bighorn, hundreds of members and descendants of 19 tribal nations gathered at the battle site to commemorate their historic victory and celebrate the resilience of their cultures. They came together in Montana to watch Native American riders on horseback charge onto the same land their ancestors did many years ago when they defeated the U.S. Army's 7th Cavalry, commanded by Lt. Col. George Armstrong Custer. Some riders wore traditional headdresses and regalia, while others opted for tank tops and T-shirts. Many carried their tribal flags as a show of unity — the same unity that enabled their swift victory on June 25, 1876. Custer's goal was to force Native Americans onto reservations after the discovery of gold in the Black Hills in 1874. Indigenous peoples living off reservations were then instructed to report to U.S. field offices, known as Indian Agencies, or be deemed hostile. Native American leaders organized various villages and tribes in a resistance effort. Numerous battles erupted in what are now Montana and South Dakota as military forces attempted to push the remaining groups onto reservations. Read about &lt;a href="http://npr.org/2026/06/27/nx-s1-5825804/native-americans-mark-the-150th-anniversary-of-the-battle-of-little-bighorn" target="_blank"&gt;what this victory means to Native descendants&lt;/a&gt; and see &lt;a href="http://npr.org/2026/06/27/nx-s1-5825804/native-americans-mark-the-150th-anniversary-of-the-battle-of-little-bighorn" target="_blank"&gt;photos from the event here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-130731" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 7008;         --source-height: 3942;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7008x3942+0+469/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F24%2F4a%2Fccbac7db4b7daa0dd1b3593877b9%2Fap26178769282052.jpg" class="img" alt="A helicopter drops water on the Cottonwood Fire in Beaver, Utah, on Saturday, June 27, 2026." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A helicopter drops water on the Cottonwood Fire in Beaver, Utah, on Saturday, June 27, 2026.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Ty ONeil/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Three firefighters were killed and two others were injured on Saturday while &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2026/06/28/g-s1-130737/wildfires-utah-colorado-firefighter-deaths-snyder" target="_blank"&gt;battling wildfires near the Colorado-Utah border&lt;/a&gt;, the U.S. Wildland Fire Service announced.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Currently, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2026/06/26/nx-s1-5860746/aca-health-insurance-subsidies-rates-premiums" target="_blank"&gt;5 million fewer people&lt;/a&gt; are enrolled in Affordable Care Act marketplace plans compared to last year's record high, according to data released on Friday.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Former Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg says that he and his children were &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2026/06/26/nx-s1-5872821/pete-buttigieg-cps-police-swatting" target="_blank"&gt;investigated by Child Protective Services&lt;/a&gt; due to an anonymous report, which was later found to be false.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
