pr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6720x3780+0+350/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3c%2Ffa%2F12e7a45e48b09c4055e36b556cf0%2Fuganda-nuns-4464.jpg" class="img" alt="Sister Mary Consulata assists an elderly nun as she takes tea at the Little Sisters of St Francis premises in Nkokonjeru, Uganda on May 12, 2026. The interaction takes place within the dining area of the congregation, where retired sisters are supported through daily routines. The Little Sisters of St Francis, a longstanding religious congregation in Uganda, provide ongoing care for aging members who require assistance with meals, mobility, and medical needs. Many of the elderly sisters have spent decades serving in education, healthcare, and community outreach across the country and now live within the convent under structured care and support." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Sister Mary Consulata assists an elderly nun as she takes tea at the Little Sisters of St Francis premises in Nkokonjeru, Uganda on May 12, 2026. The interaction takes place within the dining area of the congregation, where retired sisters are supported through daily routines.  The Little Sisters of St Francis, a longstanding religious congregation in Uganda, provide ongoing care for aging members who require assistance with meals, mobility, and medical needs. Many of the elderly sisters have spent decades serving in education, healthcare, and community outreach across the country and now live within the convent under structured care and support.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Stuary Tibaweswa for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The Little Sisters of St. Francis convent in Nkokonjeru, Uganda, cares for retired nuns. But there is minimal funding for palliative care, which offers medical and emotional support to patients nearing the end of their lives. At the convent, young nuns look after the retired nuns, helping them move to and from their beds and serving their meals. The older women lack important resources, such as adult diapers, wheelchairs, hearing aids and warm blankets. To address these challenges, Sister Jane Frances Nakafeero and Jean Callahan, who is an advisory board member of the African Palliative Care Association, started a pilot program to provide hospice support for aging nuns. Launched in September 2025, the program aims to address the nuns' medical and material needs. It will also offer psychological interventions for emotional support and mental stimulation. Take a look at &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2026/06/20/g-s1-128632/nuns-convent-africa-hospice" target="_blank"&gt;how these nuns help each other&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-129355" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5000;         --source-height: 2813;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1025px) 650px, calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5000x2813+0+447/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F3d%2Fe6%2F527ff5a643589f6ae0305fef4e84%2Fgettyimages-2259333106.jpg" class="img" alt="Clive Davis in 2026" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Clive Davis in 2026                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Leon Bennett/Getty Images for The Recording A/Getty Images North America                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Clive Davis, a music executive who helped launch the careers of many monumental stars over the decades, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2026/06/22/nx-s1-3214743/clive-davis-obituary" target="_blank"&gt;has died at 94&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The Food and Drug Administration is &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2026/06/21/nx-s1-5858691/blood-test-multi-cancer-early-detection-mced" target="_blank"&gt;assessing a blood test called Galleri&lt;/a&gt;, which could be a breakthrough device capable of detecting various types of cancer in a single test. The FDA could approve it later this year.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The U.S. Supreme Court ruled to &lt;a href="https://gothamist.com/news/supreme-court-restores-conviction-in-etan-patz-murder" target="_blank"&gt;restore the conviction of Pedro Hernandez&lt;/a&gt;, who was found guilty of kidnapping and murdering 6-year-old Etan Patz, who went missing on his way to the school bus in New York City in 1979. (via &lt;a href="https://gothamist.com/" target="_blank"&gt;Gothamist&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
